The paper focuses on analyzing the generalization behavior of existing neural network models for named entity recognition (NER) in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and machine learning. The paper also proposes measures to guide the design of models and training methods, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes the performance of models in terms of annotation errors and dataset bias, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the category relationships in NER, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
